node.text: This week Zach, our Quality Manager, helps to answer two of your questions: can you age saison and wild beers; and what is the best glassware for a lager beer? Have a beer question of your own? Let us know and we may feature it on Quality Time with Allagash.

node.title: Quality Time with Allagash - Aging saison and lager beer glassware

node.text:
Want to enjoy a perfect glass of Allagash White in the comfort of your own home? Mike is here to show you how to properly "rouse your yeast" for the optimal experience with our favorite witbier.

Have other beer-related questions? Let us know!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Mapleton, Maine with @mainemalthouse. May be an image of grass and nature.

node.text: You're looking at future batches of Allagash White. Our friends at Buck Farms carefully grow and harvest this white wheat up in the northern reaches of our state, and we'd like to thank them for it.

node.accessibility_caption:
Image 1: Chalice with amber-colored beer atop 4-pack of From Maine, With Love 08.

Image 2: Slow zoom into image of river falling over rocks with trees on either side.

node.text:
This amber ale isn't just any amber ale. Fermenting this one with a strain of brettanomyces lends a range of flavors, from citrus and pineapple to stone fruit and a tinge of funk. At a modest 3.5% ABV, this entry into our series of small-batch beers is as tasty as it is unique. From Maine, With Love 08 can be found only at the brewery in 4-packs of 16oz cans, with a portion of the proceeds directed toward helping to preserve and protect the waters of Casco Bay.

BONUS: The beautiful image of Maine on this beer’s label could be yours. Just comment with your favorite Maine river, and we’ll randomly select one comment to receive a limited edition 11x14" print of the photo featured on the From Maine, With Love 08 label.

Winners will be notified by September 8, 2021. No Purchase Necessary. Must be 21+ to enter. US residents only. ⁠Not affiliated with Instagram. Ends September 7, 2021. 1 prize. Approx. value: $25.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Portland, Maine. May be an image of drink and outdoors.

node.text:
Spend a moment taking in the view. Scenic Way, a crisp and classic farmhouse-style ale, is filled with notes of pineapple, grapefruit, and a hint of lime zest. To make this beer dry and drinkable, we brewed it with a variety of local grains, fermented it with saison yeast, and then lightly dry-hopped it for an extra boost of aroma.

You'll find this beer in four-packs of 16 oz. at the brewery and in cans across a few states up near us, including MA, ME, NH, NY, VT at your local @hannafordmkts. It starts shipping this week, so check out the beer finder in our profile to track some down near you.

node.text:
Stare into the mist, name the first thing you see.

Our deliciously dark hoppy ale, Haunted House, is lurking across our distribution. Keep a watchful eye on our locator to find it near you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Allagash Brewing Company.

node.text: Just one of the fermentors above our cellars can hold 570bbls of Allagash White. At 31 gallons per bbl, and 128 ounces in a gallon, that equals one heck ton of beer.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Allagash Brewing Company. May be an image of apple.

node.text: Golden Russet. Ashmead’s Kernel. Northern Spy. Winesap. All names of apples that we added to Coolship Pomme, our spontaneously fermented ale. After years fermenting in oak barrels and four months commingling with the fruit, this beer has come to funky fruition, featuring notes of crisp apple, oak, white pepper, and apricot, all wrapped up into a wonderfully dry finish. Coolship Pomme is now available on draft and in 375 mL bottles, only in our tasting room.
